John, I guess I have to turn you in for shrinking without a license. You have stated the case perfectly. Cognitive dissidence is a complex topic and you have boiled it down accurately and clearly.  Better that I could explain it, for sure.  It maybe the root cause underlying the whole PTSD issue, why some vets FREAKED out, and others didn't, why some vets lost it while others didn't. You must factor in the place in the jungle, of course, i.e. I have a friend who I never even knew that he served in nam. He was a cargo handler in Cam Ran Bay (sp?) and never fired a shot. The whole war was a long and sweaty bore for him.  Not like being a tunnel rat or point man.  John has it clear, just add to the formula the actual place the individual played, and sooner or later, gang, we will have the formula that will get us the Nobel Prize in Understanding.  Good thinking John.<br><br>
